I've already published how 9/7 saw unprecedented expansion of Twitter users focussed on, & increase in tweets about the aragalaya, from morning to midnight, around just the #GoHomeGota hashtag's prevalence. https://t.co/TsCJxLRfLc https://t.co/UTW0AzoeAH

PhD focused on Facebook Pages & Groups, but I also included relevant Instagram accounts. These clusters from PhD time *don't* reflect much greater diversity of aragalaya protestors on/using the app. Even with these caveats, the data signatures during #GoHomeGota are revealing. https://t.co/NbbCdCpJar

From 1/5 to 11/7, these Pages & Groups attracted over 9.5 million new likes - a proxy indicator of #GoHomeGota's growing, & widening appeal. Staggering increases on 9/5 & 9/7, led by offline developments. These are data signatures I've never studied the likes of before. https://t.co/DdvyYetE4u

Since late March, I also spent some time crafting new clusters of Pages & Groups publishing #GoHomeGota content. There's overlap with PhD clusters above, but this is far more aragalaya specific, & much larger in number: ~960 Pages & roughly same number of Groups. https://t.co/lm1Hh4Bl2v

PhD studied constellations of junk news & meme Pages. From last week of March '22, junk news ecologies shifted to enduringly feature pro-democratic, #GoHomeGota narrative frames. Likewise with meme pages. Shift was predominantly organic, & sustained. Has never happened before. https://t.co/KWKGef4UTb
